<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bewail" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bewail,</orth> to lament: <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.217" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 217</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.255" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 255</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 6, 154</bibl>. <emph>Bewailed,</emph> adjectively, == lamentable: <cit><quote>lest my --ed guilt should do thee shame,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 36.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 36, 10</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>